<p>I want to serialize a Joda-Time <code>Duration</code> instance as a long representing the number of seconds using <code>Gson</code>.  My serializer class is:</p>  <pre><code>private class DurationSerializer implements JsonSerializer&lt;Duration&gt; {   public JsonElement serialize(Duration duration,                                Type durationType,                                JsonSerializationContext context)     {     return new JsonPrimitive(duration.getStandardSeconds());     } } </code></pre>  <p>The output of this is <code>{"iMillis":900000}</code>.  I just want the number of seconds, not the iMillis tag.  Is that possible?</p>